The ELDERLY APE RETIREMENT CLUB is a collection of 5,000 Elderly Apes living out the rest of their years in their Retirement Villa. With the overwhelming success that the apes have faced, they've decided to slow down and enjoy what life has to offer. Whether it be their daily bingo games, shuffle board, or waiting for their grandkids to call, there is never a dull moment in the Elderly Ape Retirement Club.

A part of the proceeds from the sales of Elderly Apes will be donated to Alzheimer's foundations and to explore long-term partnerships.

This is an original form of digital art. The algorithm I used to create these images is new and produces a fresh and modern aesthetic. I forgot a long time ago if I‚Äôm a programmer who learned how to make art, or an artist who learned how to code. In a way, I do exactly what every artist does, copy from reality. But I designed my own brush; I created the process to express myself. All these photos were processed with a special application I designed and programmed. The technique used is called ASCII art, but with the help of new code libraries I took it to the next level. The resulting images are more pictorial than previous text art works.

data.name: Elements of Earth by David Johnston
data.description:
Elements of Earth is an ongoing collection of photos from around the world featuring earth, water, wind, and fire in order to tell the story of the power of the world in which we live. 

I designed this collection to be an adventure that collectors can take part in year after year. Each photo is meticulously created in the field and then curated to ensure only the best are included in the collection. Exploring the natural elements and designs of the earth brings me the most joy and gives me an outlet to express myself as a photographer. 

I want to dedicate this collection to my family who cheers me on and helps me live out my dreams.

data.description: I have been creating art for about 3-4 years now. As a kid, my Grandmother was an art teacher and always encouraged me to create art but I sadly never had the confidence. As I got older I quickly grew more confident and interested in creating art. Starting with music, I created music for around 3 years and quickly found out I had more interest in painting and drawing. I express myself the best I can through my art as I sometimes find it hard to do so in words. My pieces often describe stories and the feelings that I have experienced. Feel free to take a look and collect an official emotionull piece.

data.description:
Corpus  
noun

: all the writings or works of a particular kind or on a particular subject  
*especially* : the complete works of an author

Corpus is encapsuled's custom writer's smart contract. Crafted specifically to mint his upcoming works on-chain. What does it mean? The texts stored on this contract can be retrieved directly from it, without the need of any other service. The poems rely solely on the Ethereum blockchain to exist. You can go to the contract page on Etherscan and input the tokenID you want to read in the variable 15. texts.

data.name: Enchanted Game
data.description:
True Holders Count: **979**

Thousands of [Tortoises](https://etherscan.io/address/0xb8f0bb7f5d2bb0d280cc0b60675675d31c105529) and  [Goats](https://etherscan.io/address/0xb8f0bb7f5d2bb0d280cc0b60675675d31c105529) inhabit the same Island, but they don't get along very well. Stake Tortoises to generate $EGG every day. But be careful! Goats are always trying to steal Tortoises and their precious [$EGG](https://etherscan.io/address/0x81d327cf395347dd6cc0c427bb9ea77ec120e304).

data.name: Enso Water Paintings
data.description:
100 **Ens≈ç Water Paintings** were created to reward lucky buyers of my Art Blocks project [Ens≈ç](https://artblocks.io/project/34).

Dice was rolled and recorded, paintings were made with water, video recorded each painting's creation and evaporation.

I rolled a set of dice 100 times to determine each painting's features and to determine which Art Blocks Ens≈ç mint numbers should receive a free token airdropped to their wallet.

To ensure that a person would receive one, they'd have to buy 10 Ens≈çs in a row starting at #xx0 (ex 0-9 or 540-549 or 870-879). Because of that, *I* value each of these at a minimum of 1.08 Eth, but these are gifts that I'm sending out for free.

Technical info: metadata & files permanently stored on Arweave.

data.name: Entropes
data.description:
Traditional art is collected, Multiplayer art is shared.

We are a new kind of generative art that is collaborative at the protocol level. A massively multiplayer on-chain game of creation. We evolve as we are exchanged on the blockchain. When you mint or buy an Entrope, the next step in our evolution is rendered to token based on your unique wallet address (not the tx hash, though minting uses tx as a salt). Our evolution tends toward ever-increasing visual complexity, and every owner in our chain is contributing to our realization. Collectors become creators. You tell our story, together.

## Key Rules

1. Disconnects: reacquiring an entrope you previously owned within 10 transfers of the last time you owned it will result in a Disconnect. You will need to sell or transfer it to a valid owner in order for it to be reconnected.

2. Events are temporary. Some like ‚ÄúShiny‚Äù have a decay.

3. Entropes can evolve infinitely many times.

Multiplayer > Singleplayer üéÆ 
Grow the chain üå±

data.name: Especial Orbs
data.description: Especial Orbs is a limited generative art collection based off of an individual‚Äôs digital wallet address hash values. It takes the 20 values of your hash string and draws 20 circles (representative of those 20 values), places an element inside the circle and rotates that element by the value of your hash pair for that position (hash-pair-value * 1.411) to arrive at a value between 0-360 degrees. Each piece is a unique visual representation of your wallet hash values and the rotation of the inner element represents the 20 different values that are contained in your wallet‚Äôs hash string.

data.name: ETERNAL FRAGMENTS
data.description:
Eternal Fragments is a collection of 2,828 generative art pieces, fully determined by the mint transaction and rendered in 3D post-mint using recursive mathematics. 

# Utility

Eternal Fragments is Part 1 of Spectra Art's Dawn Trilogy. 

Collectors of the Dawn Trilogoy will be able to claim a Dawn Key and get exclusive benefits including presale access and discounts to future [Spectra.Art](https://spectra.art) projects.

# About the Project

The 3D generative algorithm renders fractal-like geometries and volumetric lighting to express the mint‚Äôs transaction hash. The result demonstrates the chaos and order that simultaneously arise from recursive mathematical rules.

Rarity rankings: https://www.eternal-fragments.art/#/rarity

About Spectra: https://www.spectra.art

data.name: EtherCats
data.description: EtherCats is a card collecting game, and the first NFT project to use Chainlink VRF for pack mints. The historic Founders Series, limited to 500 packs (2,500 total cats), was deployed January 17th, 2021, and sold out quickly in early March once featured by OpenSea. Each cat initially came with a verifiably random rating and multiplier which are now used to delegate voting power in the EtherCats DAO. Later on, the Founders Series was updated to include properties for the playable card game. This was also done with the support of Chainlink VRF. The highest three scores, and the highest rating of each Founders Series cat is also enshrine permanently in the EtherCats Hall of Fame. https://www.ethercats.io/hall-of-fame/

data.name: ETHEREALS WTF
data.description:
ETHEREALS are 12,345 hand drawn, randomly generated, interdimensional ghosts. Their traits are pulled from all reaches of the metaverse and include surprising mashups of cultural references all the way down to super-insider rarities. They are eternal beings that travel through time and space in search of FUN! 

For more details about the ETHEREALS story visit [ethereals.wtf](https://ethereals.wtf/) and check out our Discord!

[Jimmy Danko](https://jimmydanko.com/) is the artist behind each of these interdimensional ghosts, and is an active player in the NFT community. He painstakingly draws all the ETHEREALS by hand and then digitizes them. He is the creator behind Mayhem Island Bananas, and is known for his hyper-realistic oil paintings of toys and pop culture icons - his work is featured in private collections all over the world.

data.name: Etheretro Watch Collection
data.description: Back in the day when many NFT enthusiasts were not even born yet, Asia was producing the coolest tech and pop culture items with designs so iconic and significant that they are still in vogue 40 years later. The calm aesthetic of neon cities, anime, and lo-fi tunes is the safe haven on the internet that many of us turn to when we search for peace and balance. Our goal is to make people aware that now it is possible to own a piece of this aesthetic on the blockchain and bring the good old days to the Web 3.0. Our collection of retro-inspired NFTs will consist of 3 items starting with the watch- it is time travelling after all! For more info please visit https://etheretro.com/

data.name: Ethereum Towers
data.description:
OFFICIAL CONTRACT OF ETHEREUM TOWERS - VERIFY URL IN OUR DISCORD 

Ethereum Towers is a community-centric, vertical megastructure consisting of 4,388 resident-owned apartments and a variety of communal areas, set in the forthcoming Ethereum Worlds Metaverse.

Designed by award-winning architects, Ethereum Towers will be the flagship residence in an expanding metaverse that will provide an evolving, exciting and socially dynamic experience for all residents and visitors.

Consisting of 2 separate, conceptual towers... Ethereum Towers is made up of 4,388 apartments spanning across 101 floors in each tower. Each floor is comprised of no more than 22 apartments (Standard, Luxury and Penthouse).
